headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 30 points, Damian Lillard added 24 and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the 76ers 119-98 on Sunday in Doc Rivers’ return to Philadelphia.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat 76ers 119-98 in Doc Rivers' return to Philadelphia

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — It's no surprise that the Phoenix Suns were led by a Big Three on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grayson Allen leads balanced effort for Suns, who pull away late for 123-113 win over Lakers

headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored a season-high 33 points, Tyrese Haliburton added 17 points and 10 assists and the Indiana Pacers beat Dallas 133-111 on Sunday night to snap the Mavericks’ Western Conference-best seven-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner scores season-high 33 points in Pacers' 133-111 win over Mavericks

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen had 22 points and 12 rebounds, Caris LeVert added 18 points and 12 boards, and the Cleveland Cavaliers avoided their first three-game skid since December with a 114-105 victory over the Washington Wizards on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jarrett Allen, Caris LeVert help Cavs beat Wizards 114-105, avoid 3-game skid

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 25 points, 11 assists and nine rebounds, finishing just short of his first triple-double of the season, and the Atlanta Hawks trounced the Orlando Magic 109-92 on Sunday night to snap a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dejounte Murray steps up in place of injured Trae Young as Hawks trounce Magic 109-92

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 36 points and Chet Holmgren added 29 to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 123-110 victory over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander has 36 as Thunder win 5th straight with 123-110 victory over Rockets

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — The consistent scoring and rebounding that Chicago Bulls center Nikola Vucevic has provided through 13 NBA seasons was on full display in a gritty and gratifying road victory over a Pelicans squad that has been in good form lately.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Vucevic, DeMar DeRozan lead the Bulls past the Pelicans 114-106

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic insists he's not changing anything during his latest run of triple-double dominance, just finding the flow of the game as it comes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic has third straight triple-double to help Nuggets beat Warriors, 119-103

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 26 points and the Utah Jazz beat the San Antonio Spurs 128-109 on Sunday night to snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lauri Markkanen scores 26, Jazz beat Spurs 128-109 to snap 5-game skid

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Nick Richards had 21 points and 10 rebounds and the Charlotte Hornets took advantage of Portland’s horrible 3-point shooting to beat the Trail Blazers 93-80 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets take advantage of Trail Blazers' horrible 3-point shooting in 93-80 victory

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 33 points, Domantas Sabonis had his NBA-leading 20th triple-double and the Sacramento Kings...
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings beat Clippers 123-107 behind Fox and hand LA back-to-back losses for 1st time since December
